post_text:
EXCEL George River Internship
July 10-17 EXCEL Alaska George River
This camp is for highly motivated individuals who are interested in learning more about natural resources. Students will be involved in assisting biologists with counting salmon, sampling fish for biological data, collecting habitat information, and completing a curriculum of learning activities ranging from fish dissections to analyzing fisheries data. Students will spend seven days at the remote field camps of the George River as well as the George River Weir. The interns may receive a $500 stipend after successful completion of the program. High School Students can earn 0.5 credit in River Systems Ecology (science) or Statistics (math).
Grade Level: 11th-12th Grade
Prerequisites: Demonstrated interest and recommendation
Application Link: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1j-S5AhlM8mSktSZUbFnYQdBgPZdDSKPw/view?usp=sharing
Application Deadline: May 15, 2020

post_text:
EXCEL Math Science Expedition
August 6-13 EXCEL Alaska Aniak
The Math/Science Expedition (MSE) is an intense, 10-day float trip on the Salmon and Aniak River. Students currently in 6th-11th grade students are immersed in relevant, experiential, math, and science learning opportunities, while developing valuable leadership, employability, and character skills.
Grade Level: 6th-11th Grade
Application Link: yksd.com/cms/lib/AK01001402/Centricity/Domain/18/YKSD%20App%20for%20Summer%20EXCEL%202019-20.pdf
Application Deadline: May 15, 2020

post_text: We had a spectacular virtual holiday program today. Huge thank you to Susan Paskvan, our Native Language Coordinator, for organizing such a fantastic event. Thank you to our teachers and students who amazed us with Christmas carols in Denaakk’e, Benhti Khut’ana Kenaga’, Norwegian and English. Thank you to the special guests who joined us during this event. First, the elders from the Denali Center and in the villages: Allakaket, Hughes, Huslia, Koyukuk, Nulato, Kaltag, Ruby, Manley, Minto, Rampart, and Tanana. In addition, we had the privilege to receive a special holiday message from our state senator, Lisa Murkowski. Thank you for all your support of the families, staff and students in YKSD!

post_text: YKSD is excited about the release of the documentary entitled "Attla"! The documentary features legendary dog musher George Attla and his grandnephew, and YKSD alumnus, Joe Bifelt! The world premiere was held here in Fairbanks earlier this month followed by screenings in Anchorage. There are two more upcoming showings in Anchorage with dates already announced (November 22 and the Anchorage Museum and 06-15 December at the Anchorage International Film Festival). There will also be screenings again in Fairbanks at Regal Cinemas on a date to be determined. As a district we are proud of our alumni and celebrate both Joe Bifelt's success and the release of this film!

post_text:
In an executive proclamation Governor Walker recognizes the vital role principals hold in the education of Alaska students and proclaims October 2018 as School Principals and Assistant Principals Recognition Month.

October is also acknowledged annually as National Principals Month by the National Association of Secondary School Principals and the National Association of Elementary School Principals.

National Principals Month is an opportunity to say “thank you” to principals everywhere and to share with the community all the great work that principals do. The key to student success is a great school, and the key to a great school is a great principal. A social media campaign is held during the month with the hashtag #ThankAPrincipal used to share appreciation of your principal and assistant principal via Facebook, Instagram and Twitter.

YKSD CAREER FLY IN

This is a week long event, October 8th-12th, in Fairbanks focused on helping students learn more about careers and making plans for their future.

Application Deadline is EXTENDED UNTIL THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 27 AT NOON!
Return completed applications to cte@yksd.com

Some of the options to help students prepare for their future are: driver's permit testing, driver's safety course, driving lessons for driver's license, PSAT testing, goal setting, budgeting, communication, teamwork, career & college exploration and planning, and much more! Questions contact cte@yksd.com
Get the application here: https://www.yksd.com/Page/763

post_text:
This has been an awesome week of learning for several of our YKSD & Raven teachers. Volunteers from Pure Storage have been teaching us about web creation tools (Microsoft Sway, Book Creator, WeVideo) 3D printing, and robotics (LegoWe Do 2.0, Ozobot, Flybrix). Participants of the training will share their newly learned knowledge & skills with their fellow teachers in the Fall. We're very fortunate to have been selected for this opportunity, and can't wait to see the new opportunities we're able to offer our students.

Webcenter 11 visited the district office yesterday and interviewed our very own Judith-Hope Bates as well as the Executive Director for Pure Storage. Here's a link to the story: http://www.webcenter11.com/content/news/Rural-Alaska-District-Selected-for-21st-Century-Technology-Training-482882491.html
shared_text:

Rural Alaska District Selected for 21st Century Technology Training
text:
This has been an awesome week of learning for several of our YKSD & Raven teachers. Volunteers from Pure Storage have been teaching us about web creation tools (Microsoft Sway, Book Creator, WeVideo) 3D printing, and robotics (LegoWe Do 2.0, Ozobot, Flybrix). Participants of the training will share their newly learned knowledge & skills with their fellow teachers in the Fall. We're very fortunate to have been selected for this opportunity, and can't wait to see the new opportunities we're able to offer our students.

Webcenter 11 visited the district office yesterday and interviewed our very own Judith-Hope Bates as well as the Executive Director for Pure Storage. Here's a link to the story: http://www.webcenter11.com/content/news/Rural-Alaska-District-Selected-for-21st-Century-Technology-Training-482882491.html

WEBCENTER11.COM
Rural Alaska District Selected for 21st Century Technology Training
